fr.sorbonne_u.components.pubsub

Class Message.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.components.pubsub.Message.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    Message

    public static class Message.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    The builder class is an implementation of the builder design pattern.

    The class must control the message properties (i.e accept only String as key, and primitives as values), hence it offers the addProperty method to do perform this task. the addProperty method is overloaded to accept all primitive types.

    See Also:
    Message.newBuilder(Topic), Message.newBuilder(String)
